description:
Watch our Red Dead Redemption PC vs PS5 vs Steam Deck vs Xbox 360 performance review. 

14 years is a long time to wait, but finally Red Dead Redemption lands on PC. Ported by UK developer, Double Eleven, using lessons learned and the basis of last year’s Switch and PS4 port to power this PC release. This enhanced Red Dead Redemption PC version boosts improved visuals, longer draw distance, increased frame rates. Just what do PC owners gain from such a long wait, and is this the right time to return to the saddle?

Chapters
0:00 - Introduction
0:34 - Menu options, visual settings & PC, PS5, Xbox 360 comparisons
2:02 - PC improvements detailed and compared
4:14 - Settings performance cost breakdown and optimised settings
6:53 - Performance testing PC, Steam Deck
9:51 - Summary

#RedDeadRedemption #Gaming #IGN
title: Red Dead Redemption - PC vs PS5 vs Steam Deck vs Xbox 360 Performance Review

description: Get a deep dive into the gameplay and world of Towers of Aghasba in this trailer for the upcoming open-world biome builder game. Learn about your objectives, see combat, how you can personalize your world, and more. Towers of Aghasba will be available on PC and PS5, and it launches into Steam Early Access and PlayStation Early Access on November 19, 2024. As the junior architect of the Shimu people, it’s your mission to rebuild villages and restore ecosystems after a devastating force known as the Withered ravaged your homeland. Traverse vast landscapes, scale towering mountains, and discover the secrets hidden within the wilds of Aghasba.
title: Towers of Aghasba - Official Early Access Gameplay Overview

description:
A ruthless political struggle between Sweden and Denmark turns bloody under the tyranny of the mad King Christian II. Caught up in this deadly war, two sisters seek revenge on the men who brutally murdered their family. Check out the Stockholm Bloodbath trailer for this upcoming action, adventure, and comedy movie starring Sophie Cookson, Claes Bang, Alba August, Mikkel Boe Følsgaard, Jakob Oftebro, Ulrich Thomsen, Emily Beecham, Thomas Chaanhing, Kate Ashfield, Adam Pålsson, and Wilf Scolding.

Stockholm Bloodbath is produced by Helena Danielsson. It is written by Erlend Loe with Nora Landsrød.

Stockholm Bloodbath, directed by Mikael Håfström, opens in theaters and on demand on November 8, 2024.
title: Stockholm Bloodbath - Official Trailer (2024) Sophie Cookson, Claes Bang, Wilf Scolding
